import React from "react"; import "./about.css"; const About = () => { const skills = [ { name: "HTML/CSS", level: 90 }, { name: "JavaScript", level: 85 }, { name: "React", level: 80 }, { name: "Node.js", level: 75 }, { name: "UI/UX Design", level: 70 }, ]; const experiences = [ { year: "2022 - Present", role: "Senior Web Developer", company: "Tech Solutions Inc.", description: "Leading development of enterprise web applications using React and Node.js.", }, { year: "2020 - 2022", role: "Web Developer", company: "Digital Agency", description: "Developed and maintained multiple client websites and web applications.", }, { year: "2018 - 2020", role: "Junior Developer", company: "Startup Company", description: "Assisted in developing and testing web applications.", }, ]; return (

About Me

Get to know me better

Who am I?

I'm a passionate web developer with over 5 years of experience in creating beautiful and functional websites. I specialize in front-end development using modern technologies like React, and I'm always eager to learn new things and take on challenging projects.

My goal is to build applications that are not only visually appealing but also provide great user experience and solve real-world problems.

My Skills

{skills.map((skill, index) => (
{skill.name} {skill.level}%
))}

Experience

{experiences.map((exp, index) => (
{exp.year}

{exp.role}

{exp.company}

{exp.description}

))}
); }; export default About;
